data.description: Located in the much sought-after Jamestown neighborhood, 1616 Continental Drive W., Pleasanton TX offers an immaculate single-level home on a magnificent lot of 0.85 acres with a beautifully manicured front yard and massive trimmed oaks in the back, which showcase the sparkling swimming pool.  The circular drive driveway invites you to enter this south-facing open-plan home, which was fully remodeled in 2020. It comprises three bedrooms, two of which can easily accommodate king-size beds. The spacious primary bedroom with bay windows is on the opposite side of the home to the other two bedrooms (split floorplan). It has an excellent full ensuite bathroom with a 'knockout' shower and an extra-large and stunning walk-in closet, with ample natural light. Adjacent to the other two bedrooms is another full bathroom. A separate half-bathroom is located near the family room.  There is a huge concreted back patio area, which is ideal for those who like to entertain, or just enjoy the outdoors. A covered breezeway leads to the oversized detached two-car garage, which offers additional parking on the adjacent driveway.    Pleasanton, Texas is known as the 'City of Live Oaks and Friendly Folks' and also 'The birthplace of the Cowboy'. It offers a welcoming small-town atmosphere combined with the benefits of its proximity to San Antonio. Residents enjoy a mild climate, ample outdoor recreational opportunities, and a strong sense of community. Agriculture, the oil industry, and various small businesses buoy the local economy. This thriving and growing South Texas City reported a population of 11,004 in the 2022 census, an increase of 23% from the 2010 census. Pleasanton also boasts good schools, making it an attractive place for families. For detailed information Google 'Pleasanton Schools'. Pleasanton's rich history and annual events like the 'Cowboy Homecoming Festival' add to its charm and livability. The City Council has announced exciting plans to rejuvenate the downtown area to include new shops, restaurants, and low-rise apartments. For more information Google 'Pleasanton Downtown Master Plan'.  For more information Google 'Most Qualified Broker'.
